{{Cat main|Science fiction studies}}
'''[[Science fiction studies]]''' is the academic discipline that studies works of speculative and science fiction. Science fiction is used broadly to cover the publishing genres of science fiction, fantasy, horror, and other related non-realistic works. [[Utopian studies]] and [[futurism]] are closely related subjects, as are many relevant subfields of [[literary criticism|literary]] and [[film criticism]].
[[Category:Science fiction]] [[Category:Fantasy]] [[Category:Literary criticism]] [[Category:Film criticism]] [[Category:Cultural studies]]

